Visiting British Trade Minister Richard Needham on  Tuesday urged Japan to provide British companies with more business  opportunities, officials said.
The minister made the request when he met Japanese Foreign Minister Koji  Kakizawa, the Japanese officials said.
Needham sought Japanese cooperation in the "Action Japan" campaign  launched by his country to boost trade with Japan, they said.
Kakizawa was quoted as telling Needham that Japan would do as much as it  could to promote bilateral trade and economic relations.
Needham arrived here Monday on a visit aimed at promoting trade with Japan.
